ekit_heading_sub_title_show":"","ekit_heading_title_align_tablet":"text_center","_element_width":"inherit"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"elementskit-heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"3f978d31","settings":{"editor":"<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-pre-wrap leading-[1.7]\"><strong>Step 1: Comprehensive Smile Assessment<\/strong> <br \/>Dr. Atlas examines your teeth and bite, takes 3D digital scans or impressions, and discusses your smile goals. We use advanced technology to create a precise digital treatment plan showing exactly how your teeth will move.<br \/><br \/><strong>Step 2: Custom Treatment Plan<\/strong> <br \/>Using sophisticated software, we design your personalized aligner series showing the progression from your current smile to your ideal result. You'll see a virtual preview of your transformed smile and understand the treatment timeline, typically 12-18 months.<br \/><br \/><strong>Step 3: Receive Your Aligners<\/strong> <br \/>Once your custom aligners are fabricated, you'll receive several sets with instructions for wear and care. You'll wear each aligner for 1-2 weeks for 20-22 hours daily, removing them only for meals and oral hygiene.<br \/><br \/><strong>Step 4: Progress Monitoring<\/strong> <br \/>You'll visit our office every 6-8 weeks so Dr. Atlas can monitor your progress and provide your next set of aligners. These check-ins allow us to make any necessary adjustments, ensuring optimal results throughout your journey.<br \/><br \/><strong>Step 5: Retention Phase<\/strong> <br \/>After completing your aligner series, you'll transition to retainers that maintain your results long-term. Following retention instructions carefully ensures your teeth stay in their new positions, preserving your straight, confident smile.<\/p>","align":"left","paragraph_spacing":{"unit":"px","size":0,"sizes":[]},"__globals__":{"typography_typography":"globals\/typography?id=d210eec","text_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"},